  "active_lock_reason": "resolved",
  "body": "In [the documentation](https://hardhat.org/advanced/hardhat-runtime-environment.html), it recognizes:\r\n\r\n> Not everyone likes magic global variables...\r\n\r\nThis issue serves to focus arguments on why all magic should be removed from Hardhat by default and replaced, if at all, by an opt-in feature:\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\nrequire('hardhat').enableMagic();\r\n```\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nI do recognize that this project is not a democracy. And that no amount of upvoting or downvoting here will guarantee a change in how Hardhat or other projects set their defaults.\r\n\r\nBut perhaps there is some value in having this issue open to collect viewpoints related to the topic.\r\n\r\n",
